import pandas as pd
import numpy as np
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
df = pd.read_csv("../data/processed/security_incidents_clean.csv")
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

# Group by year and sum total affected
yearly_totals = df.groupby('Year')['Total affected'].sum().reset_index()

# Line plot
plt.figure(figsize=(10, 5))
plt.plot(yearly_totals['Year'], yearly_totals['Total affected'], marker='o')
plt.title('Total Aid Workers Affected Over Time')
plt.xlabel('Year')
plt.ylabel('Total Affected')
plt.grid(True)
plt.tight_layout()
plt.show()
# Group by Year and Country, summing the total affected
grouped = df.groupby(['Year', 'Country'])['Total affected'].sum().reset_index()

# Sort within each year and get top 3 countries
top3_per_year = grouped.sort_values(['Year', 'Total affected'], ascending=[True, False]) \
                       .groupby('Year').head(3)

# Create list of tuples (Country, Total Affected) for each year
top3_list = top3_per_year.groupby('Year').apply(
    lambda x: list(zip(x['Country'], x['Total affected']))
).reset_index(name='Top 3 Countries with Counts')

import pycountry_convert as pc

def get_continent(country_name):
    try:
        country_code = pc.country_name_to_country_alpha2(country_name)
        continent_code = pc.country_alpha2_to_continent_code(country_code)
        return pc.convert_continent_code_to_continent_name(continent_code)
    except:
        return 'Unknown'

# Apply function to create 'Grou' column
df['Group'] = df['Country'].apply(get_continent)

custom_region_map = {
    'DR Congo': 'Africa',
    'Chechnya': 'Europe',  # Part of Russia (Caucasus region)
    'Kosovo': 'Europe',
    'Occupied Palestinian Territories': 'Middle East',
    'Kashmir': 'Asia',  # Disputed territory between India and Pakistan
    "Cote D'Ivoire": 'Africa',  # Also known as Ivory Coast
    'Libyan Arab Jamahiriya': 'Africa',  # Former name of Libya
    'Western Sahara': 'Africa'
}
df['Group'] = df.apply(
    lambda row: custom_region_map[row['Country']] if row['Country'] in custom_region_map else row['Group'],
    axis=1
)
df['Group'].unique()

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import mplcursors

# Optional: global font settings
plt.rcParams['font.family'] = 'Courier New'

# Clean Group column
df['Group'] = df['Group'].str.strip().str.replace('\u00A0', ' ', regex=True)

# Group by Year and Group
region_year = df.groupby(['Year', 'Group'])['Total affected'].sum().reset_index()

# Get list of unique regions
regions = region_year['Group'].unique()

# Plot for each region
for region in regions:
    region_data = region_year[region_year['Group'] == region]

    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 5))
    line, = plt.plot(
        region_data['Year'], 
        region_data['Total affected'], 
        marker='o', 
        color='red', 
        linewidth=2
    )

    # Titles and labels
    plt.title(f'Total Aid Workers Affected Over Time - {region}', fontsize=16, fontname='Courier New')
    plt.xlabel('Year', fontsize=14, fontname='Courier New')
    plt.ylabel('Total Affected', fontsize=14, fontname='Courier New')

    plt.xticks(rotation=45, fontsize=12, fontname='Courier New')
    plt.yticks(fontsize=12, fontname='Courier New')

    # Remove grid
    plt.grid(False)
    
    # Add tooltips
    cursor = mplcursors.cursor(line, hover=True)
    cursor.connect(
        "add", 
        lambda sel: sel.annotation.set_text(
            f"Year: {region_data.iloc[sel.index]['Year']}\nAffected: {region_data.iloc[sel.index]['Total affected']}"
        )
    )

    plt.tight_layout()
    plt.show()
import altair as alt
import os

# Ensure plots directory exists
os.makedirs("../plots/total_affected", exist_ok=True)

# Clean and prepare data
df['Group'] = df['Group'].str.strip().str.replace('\u00A0', ' ', regex=True)
df['Year'] = df['Year'].astype(str)

# Group by Year and Group
region_year = df.groupby(['Year', 'Group'])['Total affected'].sum().reset_index()

# Loop through each region (Group)
for region in region_year['Group'].unique():
    region_data = region_year[region_year['Group'] == region].copy()
    
    # Get ticks every 3 years
    tick_values = region_data['Year'].iloc[::3].tolist()

    # Create line chart with red points
    chart = (
        alt.Chart(region_data).mark_line(color='red')
        .encode(
            x=alt.X('Year:N',
                title='Year',
                axis=alt.Axis(
                    values=tick_values,
                    labelAngle=0,
                    labelFont='Courier New',
                    labelFontSize=14
                )
            ),
            y=alt.Y('Total affected:Q',
                title='Total Affected',
                axis=alt.Axis(
                    grid=False,
                    labelFont='Courier New',
                    labelFontSize=14
                )
            ),
            tooltip=['Year:N', 'Total affected:Q']
        )
        + alt.Chart(region_data).mark_point(color='red', filled=True, size=80)
        .encode(
            x='Year:N',
            y='Total affected:Q',
            tooltip=['Year:N', 'Total affected:Q']
        )
    ).properties(
        title=f'{region}: Total Aid Workers Affected Over Time',
        width=700,
        height=400
    ).interactive().configure_view(
        stroke=None
    ).configure_title(
        font='Courier New',
        fontSize=18
    ).configure_axis(
        titleFont='Courier New',
        titleFontSize=16
    )

    # Save chart
    file_name = region.lower().replace(" ", "_") + "_total_affected.html"
    chart.save(f"../plots/total_affected/{file_name}")
